00:32:55,934 --> 00:32:56,374
[SPEAKER_09]: Yes.

340
00:32:57,694 --> 00:33:01,095
[SPEAKER_09]: Before I get into that, I just wanted to mention some other events.

341
00:33:02,796 --> 00:33:06,297
[SPEAKER_09]: April 26th is National Arbor Day.

342
00:33:07,851 --> 00:33:10,715
[SPEAKER_09]: So the city always has events on that day.

343
00:33:10,735 --> 00:33:20,486
[SPEAKER_09]: That's why I didn't sign up, Brenda, for the Boston Glory thing, because I'm conflicted of where I'm going to be, if I'm available.

344
00:33:20,827 --> 00:33:22,148
[SPEAKER_09]: But I just wanted you to know that.

345
00:33:22,208 --> 00:33:23,890
[SPEAKER_09]: I probably will help with that.

346
00:33:23,971 --> 00:33:24,471
[SPEAKER_09]: But anyways.

347
00:33:25,455 --> 00:33:28,656
[SPEAKER_09]: April 26th is National Arbor Day in Medford.

348
00:33:29,016 --> 00:33:35,037
[SPEAKER_09]: We're a tree city, so we always have an annual proclamation and some events around that.

349
00:33:35,597 --> 00:33:44,500
[SPEAKER_09]: Aggie Tootin, our tree warden, usually has one or more tree companies volunteer their time to trim some trees.

350
00:33:45,060 --> 00:33:46,280
[SPEAKER_09]: They may plant some trees.

351
00:33:46,360 --> 00:33:49,361
[SPEAKER_09]: I don't have the specifics yet, because it's a little bit out in time.

352
00:33:49,961 --> 00:33:54,042
[SPEAKER_09]: But the mayor usually will show up at a designated place.

353
00:33:55,297 --> 00:34:01,821
[SPEAKER_09]: And the public's invited, and they read a proclamation for the Abbott Day Tree City that we are.

354
00:34:02,522 --> 00:34:09,526
[SPEAKER_09]: In the past, Trees MadFit has also been there to have maybe free tree seedlings.

355
00:34:10,306 --> 00:34:12,348
[SPEAKER_09]: And sometimes the Girl Scouts are there.

356
00:34:12,748 --> 00:34:13,869
[SPEAKER_09]: So I don't know what time.

357
00:34:14,189 --> 00:34:15,650
[SPEAKER_09]: It's usually in the afternoon.

358
00:34:15,670 --> 00:34:19,032
[SPEAKER_09]: So I just wanted to make everyone aware of that.

359
00:34:19,052 --> 00:34:20,153
[SPEAKER_09]: That's Friday, April 26.

360
00:34:25,750 --> 00:34:26,491
[SPEAKER_09]: What else did I have?

361
00:34:26,511 --> 00:34:28,633
[SPEAKER_09]: There was something else that I didn't show you.

362
00:34:32,497 --> 00:34:46,251
[SPEAKER_09]: Oh yeah, and Saturday, during the Citywide Cleanup, Trees Benford will also be at the library on Saturday, April 27th, to give out free tree seedlings.

363
00:34:47,272 --> 00:34:51,635
[SPEAKER_09]: I don't know the time yet, so we have plenty of time to find out.

364
00:34:51,675 --> 00:34:58,619
[SPEAKER_09]: But I just wanted to, if you have a calendar and it's getting filled up, because it's Earth Week and we have lots going on, I wanted to mention that first.

365
00:34:58,979 --> 00:35:06,444
[SPEAKER_09]: So moving on to the draft treaty ordinances by Trees Met, and pardon me while I look down at all my notes.

